                                                              <dd><a href="/speaker/9524/Jonathan_Weber">Jonathan  Weber</a></dd>
                                                                                 </dl>
                      </div>
                      <div class="information_right">
                        <dl>
                          <dt>Summary</dt>
                          <dd class="description">
                            A panel of experts from the press, government, and academia discuss their new and upcoming projects. They discuss different methods of promoting investigative journalism, ranging from building non-profit institutions to converting the country of Iceland into a &quot;free press haven.&quot;<br /><br />The panel features Gavin MacFadyen (The Bureau for Investigative Journalism, UK), Chuck Lewis (American University), Julian Assange (WikiLeaks), Birgitta Jónsdóttir (Member of Parliament, Iceland) and Jon Weber (<i>The Bay Citizen</i>). Lowell Bergman moderates.
                          </dd>
                        </dl>
                      </div>
                    </div>

                    <div style="display:none;" id="transcript_content" class="tab_content">
                      	                <h4>There is no transcript for this program</h4>
                                          </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>				
