  <div class="program_landing_postbit_content">
         <div class="post_message" id="post_message_44694"><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>
					Originally Posted by <strong>Eric25001</strong>
				</div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Fine! Leak classified information!<br />
He just should be prepared to be hung after the first confirmed loss of life due to the actions.  Who is he to decide what should or should not be public?  Would this have happened in WWII?</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>WW2 was an objectively justified conflict. The Afghan one is not.<br />
<br />
More; Assange is not a US citizen and WikiLeaks is not hosted in the USoA, so has no responsibility to the US State.<br />
<br />
Yet more; the lives are put in danger because western armies have been sent on a poorly-defined and inadequately planned foreign intervention in hostile territory, so a single confirmed loss resulting from an online leak is not - compared to this fact - very significant.</div>
        __________________<br />
    <font face="Garamond"><font size="2">Francis J.L. Osborn.</font><br />
<br />
Philosophy Undergraduate, St David's College Lampeter.</font>
    
